Quadri Aruna is expected to join some of the world table tennis stars at the inaugural World Table Tennis (WTT) Champions (European Summer Series 2022). The event will be staged in Budapest, Hungary from July 18 to 23, 2022. It will see the world’s very best players coming together under one roof with Men’s and Women’s Singles events being held concurrently, offering fans double the excitement as players compete for the inaugural title. Twelve titles will be at stake in 12 days at the non-stop action European Summer Series.